Data Analysis Project By Afreen Taj(22/PCSA/115)&Ashifa Banu(22/PCSA/117)¶

1.Define your Objective¶

BEDTIME PROCRASTINATION entails a postponement of bedtime. The objective of a data analytics project on "Bedtime Procrastination" is to gain a comprehensive understanding of the factors contributing to and the patterns associated with this behavior, ultimately enabling the development of effective strategies for individuals to overcome bedtime procrastination.

2.Data Collection¶

Data collection for data analytics project on 'Bedtime Procrastination' was based on 'Surveys'. We created surveys, that ask individuals about their bedtime habits, including the time they intend to go to bed, the time they actually go to bed, and the reasons behind their procrastination which also includes questions about their daily routines, lifestyle, stress levels, and self-control. https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1TktgwxquUfjEUcaaMjULiq8-U-Cp26cGO3IDQXrGn-c/edit The dataset collected from the above form:

In [23]:
for i in df["Bedtime"]:#What time do you usually go to bed?
    j=i.ljust(2)[:2].strip()
    df["Bedtime"].replace(i,j,inplace=True)
df['Bedtime'] = df['Bedtime'].str.replace('this_string', '')
df['Bedtime'] = df['Bedtime'].str.replace('\D', '', regex=True)
df['Bedtime'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Bedtime'], errors='coerce').fillna(0).astype(int)

Feature Importance¶

In [24]:
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier


X = data[["Gender","Screen Time","Household Factors","Screen Time Duration","Awake-Experience","Sleep-Related Worries","Daytime Naps",
        "Entertainment","Bedtime","Pre-Sleep Social Media Use","Physical Activity","Bedtime Motivation","Sleep Quality Rating","Sleep Duration"]]
y = data['Age']


rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=0)
rf.fit(X, y)


importances = rf.feature_importances_


feature_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': X.columns, 'Importance': importances})


feature_importance_df = feature_importance_df.sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)


top_n = 7

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.barh(feature_importance_df['Feature'][:top_n], feature_importance_df['Importance'][:top_n], color='teal')
plt.xlabel('Feature Importance')
plt.ylabel('Feature')
plt.title(f'Top {top_n} Feature Importances')
plt.show()


print(f"Top {top_n} Feature Importances:")
print(feature_importance_df[['Feature', 'Importance']][:top_n])

from sklearn.feature_selection import mutual_info_classif
%matplotlib inline
importances=mutual_info_classif(X,y)
feat_importances=pd.Series(importances,X.columns[0:len(X.columns)])
feat_importances.plot(kind='barh',color='teal')
plt.show()

threshold = 0.05

selected_features = feat_importances[feat_importances > threshold].index

print("Selected Features =",selected_features)
